track.name: Solitude
comments: Mmmmmmmmmmm... no one like the Duke .. Ellington that is. :-)

There must be several versions popping up on people's stations.  The one I'm hearing is definitely not Django R., but is an Ellington or Ellington-esque version.  Who is the female vocal?  Def not Billie Holliday, but can't place the voice.  Wonderful, though.
Perfect for lounging under a tree in summer
I love this. The Dukes own composition,  Solitude.
Also got the version with Louis Armstrong vocals.
I'm hearing Satchmo. Someone heard Django, another person heard Billie Holiday--wonder what's up with LastFm on this one...
Sounds like a later Ellington version of a beautiful early 30's composition. Very nice.
This is most certainly Solitude! Written by Ellington, performed here probably by Django but I will try to do some research and return.

This is another misattribution. It seems to be Solitude, but must be by Django. It's certainly not a Duke version. (Incidentally, I see that someone down below was hearing Billie Holiday! Last.fm still has its rough edges.
